    <activity>
        <statement>
            <p>
                <term>Work in groups:</term> Form groups of 3 or 4 learners
            </p>
            <p>
                <term>Materials needed:</term>
            </p>
            <p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            A notebook or a sheet of paper
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            A pen or pencil
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <p>
                <term>Instructions:</term>
            </p>
            <p>
                In your groups, discuss the following real-life scenario:
            </p>
            <p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            A local youth football tournament, <em>Chapa Dimba</em> has strict age rules for its players.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            To participate, a player must be <m>\textbf{at least}</m> <m>14</m> years old <m>\textbf{AND}</m> strictly under <m>20</m> years old.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Choose any letter of the alphabet (for example, <em>a</em>, <em>p</em>, <em>y</em>) to represent the age of a player. Write down two separate simple inequalities using your chosen letter to represent these two rules.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Discuss what happens if a player is <m>13</m> years old, <m>16</m> years old, or <m>21</m> years old. Do they qualify?
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Now, try to combine your two simple inequalities into one single mathematical statement.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </statement>
        <hint>
            <p>
                For a player to qualify, both conditions must be true at the exact same time. The player's age (represented by your chosen letter) has upper and lower bounds/limits.
            </p>
        </hint>
    </activity>

